{
  "texts": [
    "Methods OverviewIn our study we were using a fine-tuned T5 Base as a reference model which shows good performance in PV-related NER tasks [31,32].",
    "Our assumption was that all larger model sizes compared to T5 Base would typically result in better performance, but it would also require more computing resources to train and run.",
    "In our experiments we strove to find the best balance between efforts and performance depending on the results of our experiments.",
    "LLMs are trained with large amounts of text data to determine the most likely continuation of an input text.",
    "The model proposes a list of the most probable subsequent words, and a text generation algorithm is employed to select them."
  ]
}